---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ImageSlot from '../components/ImageSlot.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Ladera Health Watch is a resident-led organization collecting and sharing public records, research, and community updates on public health and environmental issues in Orange County."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 pb-4 pt-10 sm:pt-14">
    <p class="font-display text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-gold-700">
      Who we are
    </p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight text-oak-900 sm:text-5xl">
      About
    </h1>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 py-6">
    <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-oak-700">
      <p>
        Ladera Health Watch is a resident-led organization dedicated to collecting, organizing,
        and sharing public records, scientific research, government data, news coverage, and
        community updates related to public health and environmental issues.
      </p>
      <p>
        The grassroots effort began in Ladera Ranch, where residents came together to seek
        greater transparency and answers regarding local health and environmental concerns.
        Reports of several recent cases of the rare cancer Ewing sarcoma within the community
        have further propelled many residents to seek information, ask questions, and advocate
        for greater transparency and accountability. As more residents from communities across
        Orange County have reached out with similar questions and concerns, the effort continues
        to grow into a broader platform for information, collaboration, and civic engagement.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our work focuses on topics such as environmental exposures, pesticide use, water and soil
        quality, air quality, public transparency, and evidence-based solutions that help create
        healthier communities.
      </p>
      <p>
        We provide a place for residents to access information, ask questions, share updates,
        and engage in respectful, fact-based discussion. By improving access to reliable
        information and encouraging civic engagement, we aim to promote transparency,
        accountability, and healthier neighborhoods throughout Orange County.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <ImageSlot subject="Ladera Health Watch volunteers or a community meeting" aspectClass="aspect-[16/9]" />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
